# Forge push always — Gitea master, GitHub mirror

**Operator standing order (2026-06-16):** Nephew and every agent **always** finish yousirjuan work with `make forge-push`. **Run it yourself** — do not ask the operator to sync manually (RL-0051).

## Canonical forge

| Remote | Path | Role |
|---|---|---|
| **`gitea`** | `git@gitea-dgx:marvelousempire/<repo>.git` | **Master** — push here |
| **`origin`** | `git@github.com:marvelousempire/<repo>.git` | Mirror (enterprise agents + push-mirror) |

**Never** push to `avery/yousirjuan` — archived.

## Required session closer (every substantive change)

After commit(s), before reporting done:

```bash
cd /path/to/yousirjuan   # or operator clone
make forge-push
```

`make forge-push` runs:

1. `node scripts/yousirjuan-verify.mjs`
2. `git push gitea <branch>`
3. `git push origin <branch>` (best-effort; Gitea push-mirror also syncs GitHub)

## When enterprise agents edited GitHub only

You do **not** need manual reconcile if timers are active. Optionally run:

```bash
make forge-sync
make forge-status
```

Timers (every 5 min): Mac LaunchAgent + DGX systemd — see `docs/setup/23-forge-sync-automation.md`.

## Forbidden

- Reporting "done" without `make forge-push` when code/docs committed
- `git push origin` alone as the ship step (bypasses Gitea master)
- `git push gitea avery/yousirjuan`
- Waiting on **GitHub Actions** — use Gitea Actions (`.gitea/workflows/`) or `make verify`

## Pipeline stage truth

Name the stage: committed → **forge-pushed (Gitea)** → GitHub mirrored → Gitea Actions green.

Full doc: [`docs/setup/23-forge-sync-automation.md`](../../docs/setup/23-forge-sync-automation.md)
